[1] List all 6 phases of SDLC in order with one line about each.
=>  Six Phases of SDLC (Software Development Life Cycle)
    Requirement Gathering :- In this phase, we collect and understand the client's requirements.
    Planning              :- We create a plan for project scope, resources, budget, and timeline.
    Design                :- We design the system architecture, database, and user interface.
    Development           :- Developers write the code and build the software.
    Testing               :- The software is tested to find and fix bugs and errors.
    Maintenance           :- he software is released to users and maintained with updates and fixes.

    
[2] Write 3 differences between Agile and Waterfall models.
=>  Agile is flexible, while Waterfall follows a fixed sequence.
    Agile delivers the project in small parts, while Waterfall delivers it at the end.
    Agile involves continuous customer feedback, while Waterfall has limited customer involvement.

    
[3] Name the 3 main Scrum roles and write one line about the responsibility of each.
=>  Product Owner – Decides the requirements and priorities of the product.
    Scrum Master – Helps the team follow Scrum practices and removes obstacles.
    Development Team – Develops, tests, and delivers the product.
    

[4] What is a Sprint in Scrum? Mention its typical duration.
=>  A Sprint is a fixed period in which the team completes a set of tasks and delivers a working product increment,
    Its typical duration is 1 to 4 weeks.
    

[5] What do these Jira board columns mean: To Do, In Progress, Done, Backlog?
=>  Backlog – List of tasks that need to be done in the future.
    To Do – Tasks that are ready to start.
    In Progress – Tasks that are currently being worked on.
    Done – Tasks that have been completed successfully.
     
